{
  "text": "In data stream computations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , stable random projections can be used at least for (A): approximating the l \u03b1 frequency moments for individual streams; (B): approximating the l \u03b1 differences between a pair of streams; (C): approximating the number of non-zero items (the Hamming norm) in a stream using very small \u03b1 [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Here we only consider 0 < \u03b1 \u2264 2; but we should mention that \u03b1 > 2 is also sometimes computed [CITATION_8] .",
